headline: 5 Revealing Analyst Questions From D.R. Horton’s Q1 Earnings Call
summary: D.R. Horton’s first quarter saw a 2.7% positive market reaction despite revenue, non-GAAP profit, and adjusted EBITDA all falling short of Wall Street expectations. Management attributed the shortfall to a slower-than-anticipated spring selling season, marked by heightened affordability challenges and declining consumer confidence.
